parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to become difficult to control, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially at high speeds or when cornering.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or jerky
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel turns unexpectedly
the vehicle oversteers or loses control
the steering force decreases or becomes erratic
the power steering assist fails to engage or disengage properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EVO system can cause loss of control, leading to accidents, especially at high speeds or when cornering.
symptoms: The power steering assist fails to engage or disengage properly
the steering wheel feels loose or jerky
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel turns unexpectedly
the vehicle oversteers or loses control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose traction or skid, leading to accidents, especially on wet or slippery roads.
symptoms: The ABS system locks up or engages unnecessarily
especially in wet weather conditions
causing the vehicle to lose traction or skid.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the vehicle to lose braking control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS applies on dry roads with no reason
the brakes shake when being applied
the brakes release braking action for 3-4 seconds
increasing braking distance
the vehicle experiences sudden loss of braking control
the brakes lock up
and the vehicle slides through intersections.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The master cylinder is leaking
the brakes feel like they have more travel before stopping
the brakes are soft or spongy
and the vehicle experiences sudden loss of braking control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the anti-lock brake sensors can cause the ABS to malfunction, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS fails to function properly
the brakes experience sudden loss of control
and the vehicle is difficult to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the 4L60E transmission can cause the vehicle to slip out of gear, hesitate, or fail to shift properly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and increased fuel consumption.
symptoms: Hard shifting from first to second gear
slipping of the transmission in overdrive
tachometer reading 1500-1600 RPM at 65 MPH
engine check light and MIL light illumination
massive fuel consumption
transmission failure
and overheating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the valve body in the 4L60E transmission can cause the transmission to slip, hesitate, or fail to shift properly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and increased fuel consumption.
symptoms: Transmission slippage
hard shifting from first to second gear
slipping of the transmission in overdrive
tachometer reading 1500-1600 RPM at 65 MPH
engine check light and MIL light illumination
massive fuel consumption
transmission failure
and overheating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The overheating of the transmission can cause the transmission to fail, leading to loss of control, accidents, and increased fuel consumption.
symptoms: Transmission overheating
transmission failure
slipping of the transmission in overdrive
hard shifting from first to second gear
tachometer reading 1500-1600 RPM at 65 MPH
engine check light and MIL light illumination
massive fuel consumption.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The replacement of the transmission can lead to further problems, including defective new transmissions, and inadequate warranty coverage.
symptoms: Defective new transmission
inadequate warranty coverage
repeated transmission failures
and excessive repair costs.
